# Merge driver for the append-only session logs.
#
# WHY: worktree sessions each append their own block to the END of these shared,
# git-tracked logs on separate branches. The default 3-way merge raises an add/add
# conflict at EOF every time two worktree branches both touched a log — the
# "cross-worktree collision". `merge=union` keeps BOTH sides' lines, which is always
# correct for append-only logs (each session's block is an independent record; you
# never want to drop one). Proven by execution: default merge EXIT=1 with conflict
# markers; --union EXIT=0, both blocks kept, headers intact.
#
# SCOPE: only files that are provably PURE append-at-EOF with zero in-place edits.
# Deliberately EXCLUDED — union would corrupt these (in-place status flips / prepend
# writer): logs/improvement-log.md, logs/friction-log.md, logs/usage-log.md.
#
# SAFETY: union silently keeps both blocks, which HIDES the rare case of two sessions
# colliding under the SAME marker header (a plain conflict would have caught it). That
# detection is restored mechanically by logs/scripts/check-duplicate-session-headers.sh,
# run post-merge by /close-worktree-session Step 4.
# Full rationale: audits/risk-checks/2026-07-17-add-gitattributes-merge-union-for-append-only-session-logs.md
logs/session-notes.md   merge=union
logs/decisions.md       merge=union
logs/coaching-data.md   merge=union
